ion of Central Heating (1T + 5L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''3. Ventilation and Air Conditioning Cooling Technician'''</span>\n* Mechanical Elements (3T, PE)  \n* Air Conditioning Facilities (3T + 4L)\n* Cooling-Air Conditioning Elements (3T + 5L, PE) \n* Control Systems, Regulation and Automation of \n: Cooling and Air Conditioning Installations (1T + 2L)\n* Mechanical Design of Cooling and Air Conditioning Installations (2L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''4. Vehicle Technician'''</span>\n* Car Systems (3T + 4L)\n* Mechanical Elements (3T, PE)\n* Internal Combustion Engines (3T + 4L, PE) \n* Control and Diagnostic Technology (2T + 4L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''5. Technical Aircraft Component Engineer'''</span> \n* Aircraft Technology (2T + 2L)\n* Mechanical Elements (3T, PE)\n* Aircraft Engines (3T + 4L, PE) \n* Aircraft Maintenance Procedures (2T)\n* Aircraft Structure and Systems (3T + 4L)\n\n; Specialties of Information Technology Specialties \n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''1. IT Application Technician'''</span>\n* Computer Networks (3T + 2L, PE) \n* Computer Programming (3T + 2L, PE) \n* Special Topics in Computer Programming (4L)\n* Design and Development of Internet Applications (3L)\n* Information Systems in Enterprises and Organizations (2L)\n* Database Management Systems and their Internet Applications (4L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''2. Computer Engineer and Computer Networks Technician'''</span>\n* Computer Networks (3T + 2L, PE) \n* Computer Programming (3T + 2L, PE) \n* Special Topics in Hardware and Computer Networks (4L) \n* Information Systems in Enterprises and Organizations (2T)\n* Installation, Management and Maintenance of Computing Systems (4L) \n* Technical Support for Computing Systems and Network Infrastructure (3L)\n\n; Specialties of Health-Providence and Well-Being\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''1. Nursing Assistant'''</span>\n* Hygiene (2T, PE) \n* Nursing (2T + 10L)\n* Elements of Pathology (2T)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n* Surgery-Surgery Technique (1T + 1L)\n* Elements of Obstetrics and Gynecology (2T)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''2. Assistant of Medical-Biological Laboratories'''</span>\n* Hygiene (2T, PE) \n* Immunology (1T + 2L)\n* Hematology (2T + 3L)\n* Microbiology (2T + 3L)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n* Clinical Biochemistry (1T + 4L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''3. Nursing Assistant (home)'''</span>\n* Hygiene (2T, PE)  \n* Infant Care (2T + 2L)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n* Preschool Age Literature (2T) \n* Muscle-Kinetic Education (2L)\n* Creative Employment in Preschool Age (4L)\n* Pedagogical Environment of Nursery Station (4L)\n* Elements of General and Evolutionary Psychology (2T)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''4. Physiotherapist's Assistant'''</span>\n* Malachi (2T)\n* Kinesiology (3L)\n* Hygiene (2T, PE) \n* Physical Therapy (2T + 3L)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n* Practical Physiotherapy (1T + 2L)\n* Physical Media and Application (2T + 3L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''5. Dental Technician's Assistant'''</span> \n* Hygiene (2T, PE) \n* Dentistry (1T + 2L)\n* Real Prostatetics (1T + 3L)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n* Elements of Orthodontics (1T + 2L)\n* Real Prosthetic and Porcelain (2T + 4L)\n* Organization-Equipment-Materials for Dental Laboratory (2T) \n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''6. Assistant of Radiology Laboratories'''</span>\n* Hygiene (2T, PE) \n* Radianthonic (1T + 2L)\n* Professional Ethics (1T)\n* Radiation Protection (2T)\n* New Imaging Methods (3T)\n* Radiotechnology (1T + 8L)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''7. Pharmacy Assistant'''</span>\n* Hygiene (2T, PE) \n* Cosmetology (1T + 2L)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n* Pharmacology-Toxicology (6T)\n* Pharmacognostic Data (2T + 2L)\n* Pharmaceutical Technology (1T + 2L)\n* Prescription-Legislation-Pharmacy Books (2T)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''8. Aesthetic Art'''</span>\n* Makeup (3L)\n* Hygiene (2T, PE) \n* Modern Aesthetics (1T + 6L)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n* Aesthetic Edge-Onyxoplasty (3L)\n* Spa and Bath Therapy (1T + 2L)\n* Cosmetology-Technology of Materials (2T)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''9. Hairdressing Art'''</span>\n* Hygiene (2T, PE)\n* Artistic Hairstyles (4L)\n* Material Technology (2T)\n* Anatomy-Physiology (3T, PE) \n* Laboratory of Technical Works (5L)\n* Basic Hairdressing Applications (5L)\n* Hair Hygiene Hair Head-Toxicology-Dermatology (2T)\n\n; Specialties of Shipping Professionals\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''1. Captain of Merchant Navy'''</span>\n* Navigation II (3T, PE)\n* Nautical English II (2T)\n* Carriage of Loads (3T)\n* \u039d.\u0397.O. Communications (2T + 3L)\n* Observance of Watching Bridge (2T)\n* Applications of \u0394.\u039a.\u0391.\u03a3. \u2013 ECDIS - ARPA (5L)  \n* Maritime Law-International Regulations in Shipping (3T, PE)  \n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''2. Engineer of Merchant Navy'''</span>\n* Nautical English II (2T)\n* Naval Engines (3T, PE) \n* Auxiliary Ship Installations (3T + 3L)\n* Observance of Watching Machine Room (2T)\n* Electrical Machines-Ship Electrical Installations (2T)\n* Maritime Law-International Regulations in Shipping (3T, PE)  \n* Mechanical Ship Constructions - Mechanical Design using Computer (5L) \n|}\n\n==Vocational education and training==\n====Vocational Training School (EPAS)====\nVocational Training School (EPAS) (\u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03a3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae; \u0395\u03a0\u0391.\u03a3.; 1970\u2013Present)) or EPAS OAED, 2 years' duration. Also known as '''Vocational Training School of Apprenticeship''' (\u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u03a3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae \u039c\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2, ''Epaggelmatiki Sxoli Mathitias''), shortened to EPAS Apprenticeship or simply to EPAS. EPAS Apprenticeship is an upper secondary [[Dual education system|two-track education system]], Dual VET (Greek: ''\u03b4\u03c5\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03c3\u03cd\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03af\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03ac\u03c1\u03c4\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2''), having alternating periods in a school with theory classroom and at the workplace with work-(traineeship) practice experience,{{ref|c|[B]}} with terms are contractually regulated by law and labour agreement. Balance between school-and work-based training: in-company (ca. 70%) + school (ca. 30%). Student insurance and two-part agreement (Greek: ''\u03a3\u03cd\u03bc\u03b2\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u039c\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2'') between the student and apprenticeship company are applied. [[Apprenticeship]] (Greek: ''\u039c\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1'') is based on the German dual learning system which combines classroom education with paid practical work in a business. EPAS is operated by Workforce Employment Organisation of Greece ([[:el: \u039f\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u0391\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03c2 \u0395\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u0394\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03bc\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd|OAED]]).<ref name=\"EPAS OAED Apprenticeship\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.cedefop.europa.eu/el/tools/financing-apprenticeships/cross-country-comparison?type_1=apprenticeship_scheme_eu&country%5B%5D=GR|title=EPAS OAED Apprenticeship |publisher=Cedefop}}{{in lang|en}}</ref> The EPAS is responsible for finding work placements for its students. Admitted students are aged from 15-16 to 23-year-old maximum who must have completed at least the first grade of the upper secondary school (lyceum). The EPAS OAED awarded \"\u03a0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03af\u03bf \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2\" (i.e. Vocational School Diploma) at HQF level 4.\n\n====Vocational Lyceum (EPAL)====\nVocational Lyceum 3 years (EPAL; ''\u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u039b\u03cd\u03ba\u03b5\u03b9\u03bf''; \u0395\u03a0\u0391.\u039b.; 2006\u2013Present)\n\n====Post-lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class====\nPost-lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class (\u039c\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bb\u03c5\u03ba\u03b5\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc \u0388\u03c4\u03bf\u03c2 \u03a4\u03ac\u03be\u03b7 \u039c\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2; 2016\u2013Present) is provided by Vocational Lyceum (\u0395\u03a0\u0391L).<ref name=\"Statute Framework of Post-Lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.minedu.gov.gr/texniki-ekpaideusi-2/mathiteia/thesmiko-plaisio-mathitias |title=Statute Framework of Post-Lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class |publisher=Ministry of Education}} Only for Vocational Lyceum (EPAL) Graduates {{in lang|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Establishment of Post-lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.minedu.gov.gr/publications/docs2019/2019.10_\u039a\u03a5\u0391_\u0395_\u0395_\u0394_\u03c3\u03b5_\u0395\u03a0\u0391\u039b_2019-20_\u03a6\u0395\u039a_3892\u0392_23.10.2019.pdf |title=Establishment of Post-lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class |publisher=Ministry of Education}} Only for Vocational Lyceum (EPAL) Graduates {{in lang|el}}</ref><ref name=\"General secretariat for vocational education, training and life-long learning (EEKDBM)\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.et.gr/idocs-nph/search/pdfViewerForm.html?args=5C7QrtC22wFqnM3eAbJzrXdtvSoClrL8PD8wzczkG7N5MXD0LzQTLWPU9yLzB8V68knBzLCmTXKaO6fpVZ6Lx3UnKl3nP8NxdnJ5r9cmWyJWelDvWS_18kAEhATUkJb0x1LIdQ163nV9K--td6SIuRZshP6o0TRW4bhfooufzfm_NDwleV7l4KzVilWSZdkd |title=General secretariat for vocational education, training and life-long learning (EEKDBM)|publisher=National Printing House of Greece}}{{in lang|el}}</ref> Only EPAL graduates and Lyceum graduates hold EPAL Specialization Diploma are admitted to Post-lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class being regarded as a separate and distinctive stage of post-secondary education (''\u039c\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1-\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03bf\u03b2\u03ac\u03b8\u03bc\u03b9\u03bf\u03c5 \u039a\u03cd\u03ba\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a3\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03b4\u03ce\u03bd''). It includes 1 year post-secondary apprenticeship dual programme (non-tertiary; Dual VET [[Dual education system|two-track vocational training system]]) belongs to the non-formal education having alternating periods in an EPAL school unit with theory classroom (1 day/week, 7 hrs per day) and at the workplace with work practice training (4 days/week, 7 hrs per day). All apprenticeships schemes should include a contract (Greek: ''\u03a3\u03cd\u03bc\u03b2\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u039c\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2''), wage and social security rights/benefits to student which is a trainee referred to simply as \"apprentice\". EPAL Apprenticeship Class programmes are based on Workforce Employment Organisation ([[:el: \u039f\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u0391\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03c2 \u0395\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u0394\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03bc\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd|OAED]]) at its dual learning principle and follow the same quality framework for apprenticeships. Graduates of the apprenticeship class will receive \"\u0392\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03af\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03a0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c0\u03bf\u03af\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u039c\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bb\u03c5\u03ba\u03b5\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u0388\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03a4\u03ac\u03be\u03b7\u03c2 \u039c\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2\" (Certificate of Post-Lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class) signifies completion of Apprenticeship Class programme. If they wish the Apprenticeship Class graduates are therefore eligible to take the National Accreditation Examinations (Greek: ''\u0395\u03be\u03b5\u03c4\u03ac\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03a0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c0\u03bf\u03af\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2'') will be held at EOPPEP examination centers. Once, they have been passed all examinations then are awarded \"\u03a0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03af\u03bf \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u0395\u03b9\u03b4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c4\u03b7\u03c4\u03b1\u03c2, \u0395\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03af\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03ac\u03c1\u03c4\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2, \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c0\u03ad\u03b4\u03bf\u03c5 5\", i.e. Diploma of Vocational Education and Training) at HQF level 5.<ref name=\"EPAL Postlyceum Year Apprenticeship Class\">{{cite journal|url=http://proson.eoppep.gr/en/QualificationTypes/Details/55 |title=EPAL Postlyceum Year Apprenticeship Class|publisher=EOPPEP Organization}}{{in lang|el|en}}</ref> Specialties of Post-Lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class coordinated by the Vocational Lyceum (EPAL) are:<ref name=\"Post-lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class, 2019-2020\">{{cite journal|url= https://www.minedu.gov.gr/texniki-ekpaideusi-2/mathiteia/43115-01-10-19-ksekinise-i-ypovoli-aitiseon-gia-ta-nea-tmimata-sto-metalykeiako-etos-taksi-mathiteias-ton-epal-periodou-2019-2022 |title=Post-lyceum Year Apprenticeship Class, 2019-2020|publisher=Ministry of Education}}{{in lang|el}}</ref>\n{{col-begin|width=87%}} \n{{col-break}}\n#Employee of Tourism Enterprises\n#Computer and Networks Technician\n#Food and Drinks Technology Technician\n#Medical - Biological Laboratories Assistant\n#Administration and Economic Service Officer\n#Conservation and Restoration of Works of Art\n#Designer of Structural Works and Geoinformatics\n#Floriculture and Landscape Architecture Technician\n#Warehouse and Supply System Employee (logistics)\n#Mechanical Installations and Constructions Technician\n#Electrical Systems, Installations and Networks Technician\n#Refrigerant of Air Conditioning and Technician of Air Conditioning\n#Electronics and Computer Systems, Installations, Networks & Telecommunications Technician\n{{col-break}}\n#<li value=\"14\">Graphic Arts</li>\n#Aesthetic Art\n#Silversmithing\n#Hairdressing Art\n#Nursing Assistant\n#Brewer Technician\n#Vehicle Technician\n#Pharmacy Assistant\n#Physiotherapist Assistant \n#IT Applications Technician\n#Plant Production Technician\n#Apparel Design and Production\n#Infant and Child Assistant Carer\n{{col-end}}\n\n====School of Meat Professions (SEK)====\nSchool of Meat Professions (SEK; \u03a3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03ac\u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u039a\u03c1\u03ad\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03c2; \u03a3.\u0395.\u039a.)\n\n====Special Vocational Education Centre (\u0395\u0395\u0395\u0395\u039a)====\nSpecial Vocational Education Centre (\u0395\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b9\u03bf \u0395\u03b9\u03b4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u0395\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03af\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2; \u0395.\u0395.\u0395.\u0395\u039a.), 6 years [[special education]] at HQF Level 2\n\n====Laboratory Centre (\u0395\u039a)====\nLaboratory Centre (\u0395\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc \u039a\u03ad\u03bd\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf; \u0395.\u039a.; 2013\u2013Present), 3 years [[Nonformal learning|non-formal]] secondary education. Admitted students must have completed at least the lower secondary education school (gymnasium or its equivalent). Awarded \"\u0392\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03af\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u0395\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03af\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2\" (literally \"Certificate of Vocational Training\"). After examinations awarded \"\u03a0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03af\u03bf \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u0395\u03b9\u03b4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c4\u03b7\u03c4\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03ac\u03c1\u03c4\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2, \u0395\u03c0\u03b9\u03c0\u03ad\u03b4\u03bf\u03c5 3\" (i.e. Diploma of Vocational Education and Training) at HQF level 3.\n\n====Institute of Vocational Training (IEK)====\n{{Main|IEK|l1=Institute of Vocational Training (IEK)}}\nInstitute of Vocational Training (I.E.K.; \u0399\u03bd\u03c3\u03c4\u03b9\u03c4\u03bf\u03cd\u03c4\u03bf \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03ac\u03c1\u03c4\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 1992\u2013Present), 2 years adult non-formal post-secondary [[Vocational training|vocational education]] and training at HQF level 5 and 960 hours at a work placement.<ref name=\"IEK Course Offerings, Law 4186/2013, Article 23, Government Gazette 193\u0391\u2019/13.09.2013\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.minedu.gov.gr/publications/docs2018/N_4186_2013_fek193.pdf#page=19 |title=IEK Course Offerings, Law 4186/2013, Article 23, Government Gazette 193\u0391\u2019/13.09.2013|publisher=Ministry of Education}} {{in lang|el}}</ref><ref name=\"IEKs Course Offerings\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.gsae.edu.gr/el/epaggelmatiki-katartisi/i-e-k-institoyta-epaggelmatikis-katartisis/odigos-eidikotiton|title=IEKs Course Offerings|publisher=EEKDBM General Secretariat}}{{in lang|el}}</ref><ref name=\"HQF \u2012 IEKs Course Offerings\">{{cite journal|url=http://proson.eoppep.gr/en/Qualifications/?page=9|title=HQF \u2012 IEKs Course Offerings|publisher=EOPPEP}} Page 9 to 24 {{in lang|el|en}}</ref> Admitted students must have completed at least the upper secondary education (lyceum) The EOPPEP organisation is the statutory body for the IEKs.<ref name=\"\u0395\u039f\u03a0\u03a0\u0395\u03a0 - EOPPEP Ognanisation\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.eoppep.gr/index.php/en/ |title=\u0395\u039f\u03a0\u03a0\u0395\u03a0 - EOPPEP Ognanisation}}{{in lang|el|en}}</ref> See a list of, click on the \"show\" below, IEK study programmes:\n{| class=\"mw-collapsible mw-collapsed wikitable\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\"  colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center; background:white;\" | Institute of Vocational Training (IEK) Study Programmes\n|-   \n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | IEK Specialties\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Departments\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Fields\n|- style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n| Forestry protection specialist \u2012 Beekeeping \u2012 Poultry farming \u2012 Greenhouse specialist \u2012 Organic and ecological farming \u2012 Technological applications and installations for floriculture and landscape architecture \u2012 Mechatronics specialist for agricultural machinery repair and maintenance  \n| Agriculture\n| style=\"text-align: left\"; colspan=\"2\"; rowspan=\"2\"; | Agriculture, <br/>Food Technology, Nutrition \n|- style=\"font-size:85%;\" \n| Nutrition and dietetics \u2012 Food and beverage technology \n| Food Technology, Nutrition  \n|- style=\"font-size:85%;\" \n| Management secretary \u2012 Distribution specialist \u2012 Customer service specialist \u2012 Secretary of legal professions \u2012 Teiresias/Individuals with vision problems/call centre operators\n| Business Administration\n| style=\"text-align: left\"; colspan=\"2\"; rowspan=\"2\"; | Business Administration<br/>and Economics\n|- style=\"font-size:85%;\" \n| Sales specialist \u2012 Logistics specialist \u2012 Insurance specialist \u2012 Bookstore specialist \u2012 IT Accounting specialist \u2012 Small business officer \u2012 Bank operations specialist \u2012 Accounting office specialist \u2012 Publishing house specialist \u2012 Real estate agent / manager \u2012  Supplies & warehouse manager \u2012 International commerce specialist \u2012 Stock exchange operations specialist \u2012 Industry - small business cost specialist \u2012 Ma