s must select 2 out of the 9 Special Subjects):\n# Nursing (1T + 4L)\n# Microbiology (1T + 4L)\n# Radiotelegraphy (1T + 4L)\n# Dental Technicians (1T + 4L)\n# Contemporary Aesthetic (1T + 4L)\n# Basic Hairdressing Applications (5L)\n# Pharmaceutical Technology (1T + 4L)\n# Introduction to Physical Therapy (1T + 4L)\n# Creative Employment in Pre-School Age (1T + 4L)\n\n; Shipping Professionals\n* Navy English I (2T)\n* Ship Electrical Installations I (2T)\n* Bridge-Engine Room Control Systems (2T)\n* Navigation I - Nautical Meteorology (3T + 2L)\n* Human Relationships-Ship Management (1T)\n* Nautical, Mechanical and Electrical Design (3L)\n* Nautical Mechanical and Applications (2T + 3L)\n* Shipbuilding Elements-Ship Stability-Principles of Propulsion (2T + 1L)\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" style=\"background:transparent;\" \n| '''Subjects of Specialties''' {{pad|26.6em}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; background:transparent;\"| Subjects of Pan-Hellenic Examinations are indicated by initials PE.<br/>Third Grade, T: Theory Weekly Hours, L: Laboratory Weekly Hours \n|-\n|\n; Specialties of \u0391griculture, Food and Environment \n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''1. Plant Production Technician'''</span>  \n* Crop Irrigation (1T + 2L)\n* Plant Protection (2\u03a4 + 2L) \n* Arboriculture-Viticulture (2T + 3L)\n* Modern Agricultural Enterprises (3T, PE) \n* Principles of Organic Agriculture (3T, PE) \n* Large Growing Plants-Horticultural Cultures (2T + 3L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''2. Animal Production Technician'''</span>\n* Aquaculture (2T + 2L) \n* Farm Animals Diet (2T + 2L)\n* Beekeeping-Sericulture (1T + 2L) \n* Breeding of Farm Animals (3T + 3L)\n* Modern Agricultural Enterprises (3T, PE) \n* Principles of Organic Agriculture (3T, PE) \n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''3. Food and Drink Technology Technician'''</span>\n* Food Safety (2T + 1L)\n* Processing of Plant Products (2T + 3L)\n* Principles of Food Processing (2T + 2L)\n* Modern Agricultural Enterprises (3T, PE)\n* Processing of Animal Products (2T + 3L) \n* Principles of Organic Agriculture (3T, PE)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''4. Floriculture and Landscape Architecture Technician'''</span>\n* Flowering Plants (2T + 2L) \n* Planning of Plant Works (2T + 3L)  \n* Modern Agricultural Enterprises (3T, PE) \n* Principles of Organic Agriculture (3T, PE) \n* Maintenance of Gardening Craft Applications (2T + 3L)\n* Applications of Irrigation Networks in Gardening (1T + 2L)\n\n; Specialties of Administration and Economy\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''1. Administrator and Financial Officer'''</span>\n* Tax Practice (2T + 4L)\n* Logistical Applications (5L) \n* Modern Office Environment (2T + 2L)\n* Principles of Economic Theory (3T, PE) \n* Communication and Public Relations (2T)\n* Principles of Organization and Administration (3T, PE)  \n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''2. Tourism Business Employee'''</span>\n* Tourism Geography (2L)\n* English of Specialty (2T)\n* Applications in Tourism (3L)\n* Principles of Economic Theory (3T, PE) \n* Principles of Organization and Administration (3T, PE)  \n* Organization and Operation of Hotel Businesses (2T + 2L)\n* Organization and Operation of Tourist Enterprises (2T + 2L)\n* One Chosen Language (French or German or Spanish or Italian (2T)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''3. Marketing and Advertising Employee'''</span>\n* Logistical Applications (2L)\n* Marketing Applications (3L)\n* Modern Office Environment (2T + 2L)\n* Principles of Economic Theory (3T, PE) \n* Communication and Public Relations (2T)\n* Principles of Organization and Administration (3T, PE)  \n* Advertising (Introduction, Creation and Display) (2T + 4L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''4. Warehouse and Supply System Employee'''</span> \n* Logistical Applications (2L)\n* Logistics Applications (3T + 3L)\n* Principles of Economic Theory (3T, PE)\n* Warehouse Organization and Management (3T + 2L)\n* Principles of Organization and Administration (3T, PE)\n* Organization and Management of Transport (2 T + 2L)\n\n; Specialties of Structural Works, Structural Environment and Architectural Design\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''1. Structural Engineer and Geoinformatics'''</span> \n* Building (3T, PE) \n* Architectural Design (Design, 4L, PE)  \n* Organization of Technical Works (2T + 2L)\n* Design of Building Projects using Computer (4L)\n* Civil Engineering and Infrastructure Project (1T + 2L)\n* Applications of Geoinformatics in Technical Projects (5L)\n\n; Specialties of Applied Arts\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''1. Graphic Arts'''</span>\n* Lettering (2L)\n* Free Plan-Color (3L)\n* English of Specialty (1T)\n* Graphic Applications (4L)\n* Digital Design of Forms (4L)\n* Material Technology (2T, PE) \n* Printing Technology (1T + 3L)\n* History of Contemporary Art (3T, PE)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''2. Silverware'''</span>\n* Jewelry Design (Design, 3L)\n* Material Technology (2T, PE) \n* Handmade Jewelry Workshop (9L)\n* History of Contemporary Art (3T, PE) \n* Reproduction Jewelry Lab - Enamel (3L)\n* Laboratory of Plastics - Metalloplasty (3L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''3. Maintenance of Art - Rehabilitation Works'''</span>\n* English of Specialty (1T)\n* Copy of Works of Art (5L)\n* Material Technology (2T, PE) \n* Cultural Heritage Protection (2T)\n* History of Contemporary Art (3T, PE)\n* Design Documentation of Art Works (3L)\n* Basic Techniques for the Maintenance of Art Works (7L)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''4. Design and Production of Clothing'''</span>\n* Material Technology (2T, PE)\n* Quality Control of Fabric (1T + 2L)\n* Clothing Production Technology (4L)\n* History of Contemporary Art (3T, PE) \n* Cutting Pattern Technology (Patron) (5L)\n* Electronic Design of Industrial Product (3L)\n* Textile Technology and Clothes Collection Organization (3T)\n<span style=\"color: #666666;\">'''5. Design-Interior Decorations'''</